<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Dikmer:
[B] You were absolutly right to part ways with this guild. For several reasons...

#1, a guild of that size raids just about every day. When can you level or make cash to restock your gem bag? They expect you to stay level 58 forever?

#2, Some people have RL issues that prevent them from spending the 3-5 hours minimum for almost any raid. This should not prevent them from logging in for an hour or so to level or make cash. Your guild had unrealistic expectations. Had the policy been, if you are online, they would LIKE to see you come, but not REQUIRE, that is different.

#3, No one (REPEAT: NO ONE) can spend all their time on raids. Take a look at the other threads I have seen here where other people complain that they spend 99.9% of their online time on raids. It is a quick and easy way to get frustrated with the game and with your guild. Which would your guild have prefered, you staying with them and raiding a couple times a week, or quiting the guild and not going at all?

#4, this is a GAME, and as such, it is for YOUR fun and ammusment. If something in the game doesn't make you happy, quit. Obviously the guild was making it not fun, and you left. Kudos to you.

I have gone on a couple raids, but for the most part, I am still in the EXP crowd. Once I break 56, that may change for me. But 2+ yellow bubs into 53, I find I would rather level than try to raid Skyshrine (or where ever). With the possible exception of Hate, as I still hold out slim hopes of someday getting EM legs or BP.[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
